<section id="tribute-info">
    <h3 id="headline"> 
      
      <p>Here is a short bio of Sara (sometimes known as Sarita) Montiel's incredible life and career: </p>   
      </h3>      
    <ul>
    
     <li> March 10th, 1928 - Sara was born in Campo de Criptana, Ciudad Real, Castilla-La Mancha, Spain.</li>    

<li> 1944 - At just 16 years old, she started to star in movies. Her first movie role was in Te Quiero Para Mi (I want you for myself). </li>
      
<li> In 1948 she became an international success with her first film outside of Spain. She led a long-term contract in Mexico. </li>

      <li>Between 1950 to 1954 Montiel starred in over a dozen films.</li>

      <li>1954 became successful in Hollywood (United States of America) in the movie “Vera Cruz”. </li>

      <li>1956 she worked with Warner Bros. another Hollywood studio in the movie “Serenade”.</li>

<li>1957 Montiel became the most popular actress and singer of 1957 and a national treasure for Spain. </li>

<li>1958 La Violetera starring Montiel broke box-office records. The theme song “La Violetera” became her signature song. The soundtrack outsold Elvis Presley and Frank Sinatra in the world market. </li>

<li>1974 Montiel retired from films and focused more on her singing career and stage performances.</li>

      <li>1990’s Montiel branched out into television with her TV series “Sara Y Punto”.</li>

      <li>2011 Montiel appeared in her son Zeus Tous’ music video “Sex Dance”. </li>

<li>April 8th, 2013 Sara Montiel passed away at the age of 85 from congestive heart failure and was buried in the San Justo Cemetery in Madrid.</li>

 <h3>     
